resources.string:
Add alert rules here.

Mode "Word":
- matches a standalone word in the message;
- example: "nd" should match "alert in nd", but should not match "fundament".

Mode "All words":
- all entered words must be present in the message (order does not matter);
- you can separate words with a space, a comma, or the "+" sign;
- example: "rocket + kharkiv" matches "rocket to kharkiv" and "a rocket is flying to kharkiv", but does not match "rocket to kyiv".

Mode "Phrase":
- matches a specific phrase;
- do not use quotation marks;
- letter case is ignored (uppercase/lowercase does not affect matching);
- example: "rocket to kharkiv" matches only when this exact phrase is present.

Tip:
- use "All words" or "Phrase" for precise alerts;
- use "Word" for broader alerts.
